eedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104dxj1665702798572.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dxj1665702798572.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dxj1665702798572.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"dxj1665702798572\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                           \n Define DTD\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Load, create, or edit Uniface-compliant Document Type Definitions (DTDs) for XML data, and map them to Uniface entities and fields.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__p_d5663e1_d5664e1_d5665e1\">The form displays the DTD in its native text format.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__section_s1m_1v2_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d450347e62\">Properties</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__ul_ogl_bv2_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__li_d2840e1_d2841e1_d2842e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xrw1665702585620.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrw1665702585620.html\" title=\"Use this property to briefly describe the development object in up to 256 Unicode characters.\">Description</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__li_d2843e1_d2844e1_d2845e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jxv1665702654504.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jxv1665702654504.html\" title=\"Text field containing the DTD's element definitions.\">Definition</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__section_djr_bv2_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d450347e89\">How to</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__ul_ayv_cv2_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__li_d2846e1_d2847e1_d2848e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qkw1665702654897.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qkw1665702654897.html\">Working with DTDs</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__li_d2849e1_d2850e1_d2851e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oed1665702655111.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oed1665702655111.html\" title=\"Use the DTD Editor to define DTDs. Uniface uses DTDs to read and write XML streams.\">Manually Defining DTDs</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__section_swd_dv2_5cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d450347e113\">Menu Options</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__p_d5678e1_d5679e1_d5680e1\">The following DTD options are available on the\n          <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File</span> menu:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__ul_qn2_2v2_5cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__li_d2852e1_d2853e1_d2854e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">New DTD</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__li_d2855e1_d2856e1_d2857e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Open</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__li_d2858e1_d2859e1_d2860e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Save</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__li_d2861e1_d2862e1_d2863e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Duplicate DTD</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__li_d2864e1_d2865e1_d2866e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Delete DTD</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__li_d2867e1_d2868e1_d2869e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Load Component\n          Structure</span>—generates a DTD based on a component data structure </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__li_d2870e1_d2871e1_d2872e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Load from File</span>—loads a DTD from\n          the file system </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__li_d2873e1_d2874e1_d2875e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Save to File</span>—saves the DTD as a\n          file using the DTD format specified in the XML standard. It does not store your changes in\n          the Repository, nor copy Uniface-specific information about the DTD to the file. For\n          example, additional properties and mapping defined for the DTD are not included in the\n          file. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__li_d2876e1_d2877e1_d2878e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Validate</span>—validates the DTD. If it\n          does not validate, view the error messages in the Message Frame (Ctrl+M). </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"dxj1665702798572__li_d2879e1_d2880e1_d2881e1\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile DTD</span>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uab1665702654218.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface-Compliant DTDs</a><p>A Document Type Definition (DTD) defines rules for the structure of an XML stream. In Uniface, a DTD is a development object that includes DTD definitions and a default mapping between the XML elements defined by the DTD and Uniface component fields and entities. It can be used to define the rules for the structure of an XML stream that is exchanged between components.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ohw1665702905473.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Examples of DTDs and XML Streams</a></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527014\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527014\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define DTD Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define DTD Load, create, or edit Uniface-compliant Document Type Definitions (DTDs) for XML data, and map them to Uniface entities and fields. The form displays the DTD in its native text format. Properties Description Definition How to Working with DTDs Manually Defining DTDs Menu Options The following DTD options are available on the File menu: New DTD Open Save Duplicate DTD Delete DTD Load Component Structure —generates a DTD based on a component data structure Load from File —loads a DTD from the file system Save to File —saves the DTD as a file using the DTD format specified in the XML standard. It does not store your changes in the Repository, nor copy Uniface-specific information about the DTD to the file. For example, additional properties and mapping defined for the DTD are not included in the file. Validate —validates the DTD. If it does not validate, view the error messages in the Message Frame (Ctrl+M). Compile DTD Related Links Uniface-Compliant DTDs A Document Type Definition (DTD) defines rules for the structure of an XML stream. In Uniface, a DTD is a development object that includes DTD definitions and a default mapping between the XML elements defined by the DTD and Uniface component fields and entities. It can be used to define the rules for the structure of an XML stream that is exchanged between components. Examples of DTDs and XML Streams Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}